Fixed code: Change the return statement to allow "0". Also ensure that if len > 1 and first char is '0', return false. So:

```
static boolean isSimpleNumber(String s) {
    int len = s.length();
    for (int index = 0; index < len; index++) {
      char c = s.charAt(index);
      if (c < '0' || c > '9') {
        return false;
      }
    }
    return len > 0 && (len == 1 || s.charAt(0) != '0');
}
```

